Package: rsmRobust
Title: Robust Multiobjective Response Surface Optimization with Bootstrap and Desirability
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R:
    c(
      person(given = "Juan", family = "Gamero-Salinas",
             role = c("aut", "cre"),
             email = "jgamero@unav.es",
             comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-0219-9848")),
      person(given = "Jesús", family = "López-Fidalgo",
             role = "aut",
             comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-7502-8188"))
    )
Description: Tools for robust multiobjective optimization using Response Surface
    Methodology (RSM). This package extends classical RSM workflows by incorporating
    desirability functions for simultaneous multiresponse optimization, bootstrap
    confidence intervals for stationary points, sequential response-surface design
    updating, and uncertainty-aware nuisance factor perturbation. These methods are
    based on the framework described in Gamero-Salinas and López-Fidalgo (2025),
    'Response Surface Methodology using desirability functions for multiobjective
    optimization to minimize indoor overheating hours and maximize useful daylight
    illuminance', Scientific Reports 15, 12173 (2025) <doi:10.1038/s41598-025-96376-x>.
